Data 

aoc.elf::aoc_get(5)
i <- readLines(here::here("2021/day-05-input.txt"))
input <- tibble(x = i) |> 
  extract(x, c("x1","y1","x2","y2"),regex = "([0-9]+),([0-9]+) -> ([0-9]+),([0-9]+)",convert = TRUE) |> 
  mutate(
    line_id = row_number()
  )

Part 1

Using map2, create a nested list for each point and then unnest and group-by+count the duplicates

p1 <- input |> 
  filter(x1 == x2 | y1 == y2) |> 
  mutate(
    x = map2(x1,x2,~.x:.y),
    y = map2(y1,y2,~.x:.y)
  ) |> 
  select(line_id, x, y) |> 
  unnest(c(x,y)) |> 
  group_by(x,y) |> 
  summarise(
    dupl = n()
  ) |> 
  filter(
    dupl > 1
  )

nrow(p1)
## [1] 5442

Part 2

Very lucky that this solution generalizes by just removing the filter!

p2 <- input |> 
  mutate(
    x = map2(x1,x2,~.x:.y),
    y = map2(y1,y2,~.x:.y)
  ) |> 
  select(line_id, x, y) |> 
  unnest(c(x,y)) |> 
  group_by(x,y) |> 
  summarise(
    dupl = n()
  ) |> 
  filter(
    dupl > 1
  )

nrow(p2)
## [1] 19571

I am unbelievably excited to have placed in the top 500!

And per Joes request, a plotses!

input |> 
  mutate(
    x = map2(x1,x2,~.x:.y),
    y = map2(y1,y2,~.x:.y)
  ) |> 
  select(line_id, x, y) |> 
  unnest(c(x,y)) |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y, color = line_id, fill = line_id, group = line_id)) + 
  geom_line() + 
  labs(
    title = "Advent Of Code Day 5: Hydrothermal Venture",
    caption = "@_TanHo"
  ) + 
  tantastic::theme_tantastic() + 
  theme(
    axis.title.x = element_blank(),
    axis.title.y = element_blank(),
    legend.position = "none",
    axis.text.x = element_blank(),
    axis.text.y = element_blank(),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)
  )
